s disease patients. Thus, neurofibrillary tangles are a critical feature in the pathology and symptomatology of this neurodegenerative disorder.", "NEUROGENIC ANOREXIA:", "NEUROLEARN:NeuroLearn is a digital therapy platform that monitors brainwave changes during learning to optimize treatment for depression", "NEUROLOGY:", "NEUROPATHOLOGY:", "NEUROSIS:Neurosis is a broad category of mental health disorders characterized by chronic distress without the presence of delusions or hallucinations, distinguishing it from more severe psychiatric conditions. Historically, it has been defined as a functional disorder of the nervous system, setting it apart from organic diseases. Neurosis encompasses a range of conditions, including anxiety disorders, panic disorders, and hysteria, and often overlaps with symptoms of neurasthenia. While it involves significant emotional and psychological discomfort, it does not entail a severe loss of contact with reality, making it distinct from psychotic disorders. This term has been used to describe a spectrum of mental health issues that impact daily functioning but remain within the realm of functional, rather than organic, disturbances."], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-v3"}}}